title: Dolphins tackle Branden Albert returns to practice on limited basis; tight end Sims still out
text:
Dolphins tackle Branden Albert returns to practice on limited basis; tight end Sims still out THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   5:13   5:13   
People: 
Florida (987) 
DAVIE, Florida — Miami Dolphins left tackle Branden Albert has returned to practice on a limited basis after missing last week's loss to Buffalo. 
Albert was sidelined by a right hamstring injury and is still recovering from reconstructive left knee surgery in November. He limped Wednesday as he took part in some drills. 
The Dolphins' offensive line was woeful without Albert in Sunday's 41-14 loss to the Bills. Miami plays the Jets in London on Sunday. 
Tight end Dion Sims (concussion) did not practice. Tight end Jordan Cameron (groin) and defensive tackle Earl Mitchell (back) were limited with lingering injuries.
